== Jasmine Rice ==

Pour the @Water for the Rice{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting
lid.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @Salt{¼%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once
boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the #pan{} from the heat (still
covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to
serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Pickled Carrot ==

Meanwhile, trim and peel the @Carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long
ribbons down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

In a #medium bowl{}, add the carrot ribbons, @Rice Vinegar{15%ml} and @Sugar{½%tsp}.
Season with @?salt{} and @?pepper{} and toss to combine. Set aside to pickle.

== Chicken Nuggets ==

In a medium bowl, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g}, @Cornflour{20%g}
and @?salt{}. Toss to coat, then set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

Trim the @Pak Choi{1}, then thinly slice widthways. Peel and grate the @Garlic
Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Stir-Fried Pak Choi ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat. Add the
pak choi and stir-fry until just soft, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds} more. Transfer to a #bowl{} and
cover to keep warm.

== Teriyaki Glaze ==

Return the (now empty) #pan{} to medium-high heat with a drizzle of
@oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, fry the cornflour chicken until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn
frequently to ensure it doesn't burn.

Stir in the @Teriyaki Sauce{100%g}, @Miso Paste{15%g}, @Sambal Paste{15%g} and
@Water for the Sauce{50%ml}. Stir to combine and toss to coat the chicken.
Bring to the boil, then remove from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

== To Serve ==

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the carrot pickling liquid.
Share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the chicken nuggets, pak choi and pickled carrot in separate sections
over the rice. Enjoy!